THE Lagos State Command of the Federal Road Safety Corps (FRSC) has said it is working with the police and military to counter robbery attacks on the long bridge, on the Lagos-Ibadan highway. The News Agency of Nigeria (NAN) reported that robbers seize the opportunity of the gridlock between the bridge and Berger Bus-stop on the highway to dispossess motorists and commuters of their valuables. The section is currently undergoing reconstruction by the Federal Government, hence the partial closure which causes gridlock on the highway. ALSO READ: 20 women groups storm Kano Assembly, protest kidnap of nine children 50m Lagos commuters used BRT in 10 months says MD One dies, seven injured in Ondo road accident Saleswoman docked for allegedly stealing employer’s N4.1m Engineer, 44, arraigned over alleged assault, breach of… The state FRSC sector commander, Mr Hyginus Omeje, told NAN on Monday in Lagos that the corps was aware of cases of robbery attacks on motorists on the long bridge and had risen to the occasion. Omeje said since FRSC officers do not carry arms, the corps is working with relevant agencies to clamp down on the miscreants who capitalise on the gridlock to rob people. “Whatever we need to do to reduce gridlock across the state, we have to do it. It is because of this gridlock that miscreants attack people in traffic. “Some of these miscreants are armed to dispossess people of their jewellery, phones and other valuables. SHOCKING LIFE STORY!!! Abuja Man reveals (FREE) secret Fruits that Increased his Manh0d size and Lasting Power in just 7days… CLICK HERE
